00:22:37.390 --> 00:22:40.840
Of course if, you didn't know
what the height of these things

00:22:40.840 --> 00:22:45.910
is, then you might have to
use some iterative algorithm

00:22:45.910 --> 00:22:51.250
in order to come up with
the best reconstruction.

00:22:51.250 --> 00:22:53.350
You can imagine also that--

00:22:53.350 --> 00:22:56.860
so this is for this
so-called 2 and 1/2 D object.

00:22:56.860 --> 00:23:01.450
You could imagine an object
which really did have structure

00:23:01.450 --> 00:23:04.390
inside itself, so
maybe these three Ms

00:23:04.390 --> 00:23:09.940
would be on top of each
other and semi-transparent.

00:23:09.940 --> 00:23:13.990
And then the trick would
be to try to actually

00:23:13.990 --> 00:23:21.270
produce a reconstruction of the
3D object from the 3D image,

00:23:21.270 --> 00:23:24.990
and there are actually
computer packages

00:23:24.990 --> 00:23:29.360
